 to hold breath, then it must also hold message, because information is a tide and tides do not honor walls without preparation and respect. I will not let the Loom choke the messenger, nor the Kilns bribe the signal, nor the Wardens dam the rumor until it bursts and drowns us all. Write a lane for green flame, a truce path that no faction may toll, so that when the city must hear itself, it can, swiftly and without knives. Do this, and the Grey Lanterns will shutter their lamps to spell truths even stones can read, and lies will warp like cheap glass under a proper heat.\"},\n        {\"speaker\": \"Iriel Vask\", \"lines\": \"We do not pour breath into a treasury; we give the city lungs, and lungs do not hoard air, they move it, and music is the proof they are working. The cord will not tie us to a master if we tune it to a shared pitch, and that pitch lives where we hold back our cruelty and spend our strength with care. I can sound the Fourth-Rib bone flute and let the menhirs answer, their resonance mapping the safe knots where the breath will dwell without fraying the grammar of our names. We can braid margins into the weave, spaces that flex with flood and famine, that forgive without forgetting, that reckon without revenge. If we agree to be kinder with our strength and stingier with our cruelty, the breath will hold us to it like a song you cannot forget even when anger makes your hands shake for a blade.\"}\n      ],\n      \"choices\": [\n        {\"id\": \"C1\", \"title\": \"Braid of Equals\", \"text\": \"Iriel proposes an accord that distributes voice and responsibility across all named factions present, committing the breath to a balanced braid that no single guild can tighten or slacken alone. They speak of a shared pitch verified at dawn and dusk by the Bone Bell’s silent sympathy, making abuse audible in the city’s very timbre so any citizen can hear it and cry foul. The plan builds in margins that flex during flood or famine, codified triggers that 